WEBVTT

00:01.490 --> 00:07.220
One of the beauties of working with spreadsheets presentations documents in Google Apps for business

00:07.490 --> 00:13.800
is the ability to share obviously and the ability to add comments that can be disseminated across anybody

00:13.800 --> 00:15.440
you're sharing this with.

00:15.440 --> 00:19.940
Now remember if I come up here we are sharing this with me.

00:20.000 --> 00:22.080
I'm pretending to be Bonnie.

00:22.100 --> 00:24.540
Bonnie wants to leave me a comment.

00:24.590 --> 00:26.110
Now could be a presentation.

00:26.240 --> 00:27.280
It could be a document.

00:27.320 --> 00:28.440
Works the same way.

00:28.640 --> 00:34.580
In this case select maybe a cell that you want to attach the comment to which I just did.

00:34.610 --> 00:36.490
You can click this button right here.

00:36.860 --> 00:42.160
You can click this button right here you go up the word insert and good on the comments over here doesn't

00:42.170 --> 00:44.220
matter where you do it you're going to get the same thing.

00:44.360 --> 00:49.430
So we have that cell selected and we come up here and we click say here insert it.

00:49.460 --> 00:52.220
Now notice what happened down here first.

00:52.440 --> 00:55.850
It's telling me the sheet now will have a comment on it.

00:55.950 --> 00:58.610
Any sheet that has a comment will have that icon.

00:58.860 --> 01:01.650
Let's get back over here and type in.

01:01.650 --> 01:03.900
What do you think of this format.

01:04.620 --> 01:06.040
Go and click that.

01:06.070 --> 01:07.960
So she now has that comment right there.

01:07.960 --> 01:14.640
Notice the little tiny dog ear right in that corner which shows you where that comment is.

01:14.770 --> 01:19.860
Now let's do maybe another one up here is blue the right color.

01:21.930 --> 01:27.420
If at any time she wants to see her comments then she can do it just by touching them hovering.

01:27.450 --> 01:30.050
But if you click up here on comments they will appear.

01:30.210 --> 01:32.390
But don't forget she's sharing this with me.

01:32.610 --> 01:33.990
So let's go ahead and do this.

01:33.990 --> 01:35.830
Let's come back out of here.

01:36.740 --> 01:39.370
Let's go ahead and log out of Bonnie.

01:39.370 --> 01:40.240
Sign up.

01:40.670 --> 01:43.400
Let's go in to meet.

01:43.600 --> 01:46.860
Let's come over here and go into shared with me.

01:46.980 --> 01:52.810
And there it is sharing in the I can come into it and open it up and you can see I can come over to

01:52.810 --> 01:55.340
these right here and see them.

01:55.510 --> 01:57.440
I can also respond.

01:57.460 --> 02:01.060
Send it back in when the Google server saves my comments.

02:01.060 --> 02:08.020
If she's online she can actually work with it back and forth comments are a great way to collaborate

02:08.020 --> 02:09.940
on things as complex as spreadsheets.

02:09.940 --> 02:11.390
Make sure everything is right.

02:11.410 --> 02:15.970
But as long as it's being shared and I can share this or she can share this with as many people as she

02:15.970 --> 02:16.850
wants.

02:16.930 --> 02:21.720
That's where the power of Google Apps for business really begins to shine.

02:21.760 --> 02:25.400
Doesn't matter if it's a spreadsheet a presentation a document doesn't matter.

02:25.420 --> 02:31.780
Being able to communicate from any point on the planet back and forth in real time is a tremendous asset.
